node.text: Sometimes it just helps to have a visual! Here are step-by-step instructions for how to install our highchair footrests. 🤗 In order for the new cut-outs to hide the support clamps and allow the footrest sit at a 90 degree angle, you need to have the deeper part of the groove facing forward. That’s the biggest change in this new design! As always, if you have any questions or trouble, you can email support@yeahbabygoods.com for help! 😘

node.text:
Ever wonder about the new product development process? I thought it would be fun to make a video and take you through the thought-process, the prototypes, the launch, and the iterations of our highchair footrest. It’s been a wild two years! What I really LOVE is that the initial idea and every change/improvement we’ve made came directly from YOU, our amazing followers. We appreciate your suggestions and feedback more than you could imagine! 💕

Have you bought a YBGs footrest? At what point in the process did you join the club? 😁

📷: @this.house.of.boys

Since so many people ordered leg wraps during our Black Friday sale, I wanted to repost our installation video so it’s easy to find!

❗️BEFORE INSTALLATION, PLEASE CLEAN YOUR LEGS WITH RUBBING ALCOHOL AND LET DRY❗️

This video shows how to install the precut leg wraps with the legs OFF the highchair. You start at the bottom and work your way up so it won’t matter if you have the old or new IKEA highchair leg style, which are slightly different lengths. If you are slow and careful as you smooth down the sides one at a time, there should be very little bubbles. If some bubbles do appear, use your fingernail to rub them towards the seam.  
 
[NOTE: You can still use the install method with the legs attached to the highchair and work your way down, but if you have the older, shorter legs, you will have more to trim at the foot (or you will want to trim about 1/2 inch off before installing).]

As promised, here is an installation video and tutorial on how to modify our precut strips if you have the longer style legs. (Please watch the IGTV video called “HUGE UPDATE ON PRECUT LEG ADHESIVES” if you haven’t already! It’s important to know about the different highchair legs before purchasing.) 
 
As I mentioned in my last video, IKEA started rolling out the newer style legs in 2018 but it’s important to check your highchair legs before ordering (sometimes the product date is a lot earlier than the purchase date!). You can look to see if the top is straight (older style legs) or bent (newer style legs). You can also measure: 
▪️Older style IKEA ANTILOP legs: 28 7/8 inches from top to bottom 
▪️Newer style IKEA ANTILOP legs: 29 3/8 inches from top to bottom 
 
The strips we are launching tomorrow are made to fit the older (shorter) style legs.  This video shows a modification that can be used if you have the newer (longer) style legs, but it does require two sets of leg wraps. This is why we are currently offering these leg wraps for a 50% discount. New leg wraps will be released around the end of October if you want to wait for wraps that provide full coverage on both style legs. 😊 
 
Who thinks they might be interested in purchasing tomorrow??

We are doing a soft launch with our restock ✨tomorrow✨...but there is a big caveat. PLEASE WATCH THIS VIDEO IN ITS ENTIRETY BEFORE ORDERING! 

At @yeahbabygoods, we place a really high value on transparency. Sometimes that includes cute family videos and exciting restock numbers. Other times, it’s sharing losses and setbacks. That being said, here’s an update on our precut leg adhesive wraps...

IKEA has been making the ANTILOP highchair for years. Around 2018, they started rolling out a newer style leg that has a slight bend at the top that makes them just a little longer (please note: the older style legs were not recalled and are still safe to use). When we measured for our leg adhesives, we somehow had an older set of legs on the chair. 🤦🏼‍♀️ 

Of course, when we realized these are about a quarter inch too short on the newer style legs, I wanted to curl up in a corner and never come out. But that’s not the small business way, and it’s not the Team Kruithof way either. We want to show our kids that mistakes happen, money is lost, things don’t always work out perfectly...and then you rise up and figure out next steps. You keep perspective, you learn from mistakes, you don’t let it rob your joy. 

Here’s what we decided to do: We will be doing a soft launch with these “older leg style” wraps with Monday’s restock. What do I mean by “soft launch?” Just that we don’t have the professional pictures and videos and we aren’t promoting like crazy. Our first priority is to make sure everyone watches this video and knows what they are getting before purchasing. The installation video will show a modification that can be used if you have the newer style legs, but it does require two sets of leg wraps. THIS IS WHY WE WILL BE OFFERING THE WRAPS FOR A 50% DISCOUNT ($6 for a set of 4). 

We are also rushing to produce revised wraps that will provide full coverage on both style legs. We expect those to be ready end of October. 

Thank you all for loving our family and business so well. This is a community with so much grace and I appreciate you all more than I can say! Please send us an email if you have any questions!

We've been making highchair accessories for 4.5 years now. The first 3.5 were slow and steady. We had a happy little following of about 20k followers and were so thankful to be getting around 15 orders a day. Then, fall of 2019, big things started happening. It was honestly the most divinely appointed sequence of events, and I can only point to a Heavenly Orchestrator who had bigger plans than I imagined for @yeahbabygoods. 
 
1) On September 3rd, I changed my entire approach to IG. I'm going to share more about this at the one year anniversary! 
2) On November 15, we launched our adjustable bamboo footrest. We sold 200 footrests in less than 2 minutes. 
2) On January 9, @ryanandrose, a family-run paci clip company with 1M diehard followers, partnered with us for a giveaway. 
3) On February 18, @aspynovard, an adorable instagrammer with 2M followers, shared about us on her stories.  
 
I believe these four things changed the course of our little business. God smiled down on @yeahbabygoods and blessed us immensely. We've gained over 50K followers in the last year. 😮
 
I can't tell you how thankful I am to Aspyn for sharing about us on her YouTube channel and instagram. I constantly hear from new followers that they found us through her referral. I was looking through Aspyn's past YouTube videos the other day and found her daughter's first solids. I thought it would be fun to share her clip along with these reflections. I have no idea where we will be in another year. Sales or followers may be up or down from where we are now, but God's goodness isn't measured by that kind of success. For us, small business life has been all about taking each new twist and turn in stride and trusting God throughout the highs and lows! 
 
Who’s your favorite YouTuber or instagram mama to follow? Where do you like to find out about new baby products? 
 
🍎 AUGUST GIVEAWAY 🍎  
Comment on our August posts for a chance to win a free cushion cover ($34 store credit). We’ll announce the lucky person on August 31st!

My husband and I started making accessories for the $20 IKEA highchair back in 2016. If you are just joining us, this is an exciting time! We are restocking footrests at the end of this month, launching a new, super fun website in about a week and hoping to offer multiple new products by the end of the year! I hope you enjoy following us, getting to know our family, and seeing all the ways you can completely customize your highchair! ❤️

I’d love to know how you found us, and if you already have an IKEA highchair or are not yet! Answer in the comments and you could get a free cushion cover! Details below! 👇🏻

Anybody else loving the colors @5littlebirds_ used for little Navy’s first birthday!? Here’s a neat story…I first “met” @5littlebirds_ mama Charisma on IG when she tagged our shop. Since then, we have become good friends, swapping encouragement and family traditions. She even sent Covey several packages of Navy’s hand-me-downs. 😍 

Social media can sometimes be a distraction or comparison trap for me, but it’s awesome when God uses it to connect two people who may not have otherwise met. Charisma has been a source of light in my life this last year, as well as many of my other followers! I’m incredibly thankful for the kind and supportive @yeahbabygoods community! Not only do you build me up, but I often see you encouraging each other in our comments as well. ❤️ 

Hmmm, this is making me think…maybe I should start a monthly kindness giveaway where I get to bless someone who is encouraging others in our comments with some store credit! 🤔🥰
